PHOENIX (The Borowitz Report)—After her failed bid for the US Senate made her a two-time loser, an irate Kari Lake complained on Monday that it was “totally unfair” that the Republican Party had suddenly decided to accept election results.
“I thought we were going to have frivolous lawsuits and baseless claims of voter fraud like we always do,” she said. “I no longer recognize my Republican Party.”
“Where are all the election deniers when you need them?” asked Lake, who now calls herself “an election denier denier.”
“Where’s the QAnon Shaman?” she demanded. “Where’s Ginni Thomas? I haven’t seen one frickin’ Proud Boy marching for me. You people all suck!”
commentText: That’s a lot of words for “no one will sleep with me”…

postText:
Green Party of Tennessee ~
The party for the people, planet and peace.

https://www.facebook.com/greenpartyoftennessee
commentText: I don’t know if any of my ancestors fought mountain lions, but I do know that my (paternal) Grandma fought the wind and weather to bring in crops to feed her children while my grandfather was off chasing women and booze. I know that my (maternal) Grandmother, my great-aunt, and my great grandmother fought the patriarchy for the vote, for education, and for job opportunities— a fight I have fought my entire adult life and will continue to fight for whatever years remain to me. My daughters also fight the good fight. Those crows feet are a badge of honor and a sign of a life well lived.

postText: Friends from Uzbekistan in Brooklyn,  New York ,  USA
commentText:
I have a lot to show for my life. 10 years higher education. I owned 2 businesses, was a piano teacher, worked for the number 2 university in Florida for the number 1 ( at that time) division 2 football team in the country. I spent many years in spiritual music leadership, lay speaking, and leading yoga intensives and retreats. I have more certifications than can fit on a standard 2 page resume. I spent my life teaching, nurturing,  and guiding children. I have 3 children through an abusive fundamental Christian marriage. My ex husband beat us and raped my daughter. He will be in prison until he is in his 90s. The child he raped passed from complications from a congenital heart defect after battling a fentanyl addiction from trying to cope with the ptsd he caused from the abuse. My other kids are doing well after years of therapy and hard work. I went on and dated after, but every man I met either lied and cheated, jumped off into drugs, wanted 6 girlfriends, or ran out the door when he found someone new he wanted. I saw it at pointless. The ones I encountered lacked the character, empathy, and devotion to sustain intimate relationships. 
Today I help women who are running into similar circumstances learn self care, develop lives free of the drama of romantic entanglements, become educated, develop hobbies  spiritual connection, and good female friendships to enjoy life to the fullest! Men who talk like the one on here think our lives are meaningless because they don’t revolve around their needs. Their vision is limited to seeing us as property, indentured servants, and existing to meet their needs. My life is incredibly fulfilling and meaningful! I am important to the  women and children I interact with, the ones who benefitted from my educational and career pursuits, and those wanting to learn how to break free of patriarchal conditioning and abusive relationships. Seeing our young women break free of limiting ideas and constricting roles has been more much fulfilling than cooking good meals, washing laundry, and catering to the sexual desires of men who treated me like I was less than, irrelevant, and disposable ever was! To me, God placed them in my life to teach me there was a better life out there than the one society said was supposed to be be fulfilling. 
My legacy doesn’t just live on through my children. It lives on in the changed lives of the people I interacted with. The principles of 4b are spiritual. I learned them through a Brahmacharya vow. Vows like these lead to immense personal growth and development, physical health and well being, increased connection with God, character development, and deeper personal relationships. Satisfying a man’s stomach and sexual organs can not come close to that!

I see women who feel completely mired in the subject of what her role is in society, totally embroiled in all the conflict, and stuck where she is in life. I also see a lot of women who would never do anything to change that situation either.

Richard Dawkins is a man I have a lot of respect for, because he is key to turning people’s perspectives around and he sees the role religion plays in oppressing women. 

One of the worst situations I see a woman face is her choice to be in the type of home she always grew up in, and then evades the subjects her man does constantly, being a fervent believer in her religious practices, condemning every other person in her life.

When women are going to openly condemn a group of people who are not a part of a male dominated environment, and then she also looks for any opportunity to retain control and have power in a relationships while transferring all her responsibility to someone else who will be blamed for her actions when they were the owners of property but she remained in possession of it, and someone else was held accountable for what she did, she is not helping her case that she is not as culpable as any other man who would suppress another person. 

What level of support do we provide her? She hurt people, and she needs to be held accountable in the case I’m describing.

[Malik Tariq Awan](https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100014635304045&__tn__=R) hello. they are goats of the Valdosta race, bred mainly in the Alps of the North West of Italy (in the regions of Piedmont and Valle d'Aosta). They are raised by small and very small breeders who appreciate them especially for their peculiar appearance. there are also people who use their milk, but they mainly raise them for meat or to sell animals (both male and female) to other enthusiasts. the total number of heads of this race is 4-5000
commentText:
While women's suffrage has made significant progress globally, there have been instances where women's voting rights were restricted or revoked.

In Afghanistan, women's right to vote was taken away after the Taliban came to power in 1996. Although women's suffrage was restored in 2001, the current Taliban regime has imposed severe restrictions on women's rights, including their right to vote .

In Iran, women won the right to vote in 1963, but after the 1979 revolution, women's rights were severely curtailed. Although women can still hold public office, they face significant barriers and are underrepresented in politics .

These examples highlight the ongoing struggles women face in exercising their right to vote and participate in the democratic process.

postText:
Has anyone cooked a turkey from a frozen state in the IP?  My husband has pneumonia so we have gone from the large family gathering in a restaurant to just the two of us. Trying to retain some semblance of Thanksgiving so found a small turkey but it’s frozen. Instructions say it can be cooked frozen (don’t think it will thaw overnight). Have no idea about timing.

Update:  I took all of your suggestions and mush them into a plan. Soaked the 3 pound turkey overnight in the Insta pot pot in cold water. It seemed perfect to cook so I put it in the pot with some seasoning and poured some chicken stock to the bottom and set the turkey on a rack. Set the timer for poultry setting (duh!) which was 15 minutes. Just checked and it’s perfect.

Thanks for all the suggestions. I probably could have figured it out myself, but it was the frozen part that had me rattled. I was afraid it wouldn’t defrost in time to cook.

postText:
Tonight was my first try and although it was delicious I feel as if it was a total fail! I did search the site before posting this but did not find answers! Several questions I could not find answers to….
1- got a burn notice immediately upon cook time starting. Didn’t know what to do so grabbed the instruction manual but turned it off. When searching burn notice on this group I see many saying to open to top and make sure there is enough liquid. I thought you couldn’t open the cover when under pressure??
2- recipe just stated “pressure cook”. How do you know if you use low or high pressure?
3- , i was making chicken parm. Did the saute then added liquid and deglazed, pasta next with the chicken on top. It got to pressure then burn notice. As I said I turned it off then. Once I released the pressure and opened it the chicken was cooked to perfect temp. So if I had let it go thru the 6 minute cook cycle I wonder if it would have been overcooked??

postText:
Update: I did end up running it through a fine mesh strainer and feel better about it.

Ok, this is first time making turkey (or any kind) bone broth, so please be kind. Does this color look right? I cooked half of a bone in turkey breast carcass with a medium onion, some celery, carrots, a splash of apple cider vinegar and bay leaves for 2.5 hrs pressure on the soup function and allowed it to do a full natural release which took about 45ish minutes. I used the steamer basket which made it super easy to pull everything out. Everything fell right off the bone. The turkey however was super dry and there were lots of tiny bones, so I won’t be using the meat. Does the broth need to be run through a finer strainer? If so, I’ll need to go out and get one tomorrow. I see some itty bitty specks of things circling, but they seem soft. It’s gelling up now as it’s cooling, so that’s good. Thank you!

postText:
Yesterday I made Two Sleevers (Urvashi Pitre) Butter Chicken and oh. my. goodness. 

Urvashi mentions in the recipe that it's so good she could drink the sauce. "how great can this sauce be?" I thought, full of doubt. Then ...I licked the spoon after giving the "butter" and "cream" a final stir. 

Heaven in my mouth.

Even with Smart Balance butter and plain Greek yogurt, this dish was incredible! My fiancé had a hard time grasping what "butter chicken" was ("is the chicken greasy? does that mean the sauce is just 'butter sauce?!'"), but happily devoured a bowl and a half of rice drenched in the just-spicy-enough sauce. 

Four thumbs WAY up. 👍👍👍👍 We're going to try it with tofu for our "later" portion. I'm sure it will be just as finger licking (ew, just kidding I don't condone that) good.

 https://twosleevers.com/2017/03/now-later-butter-chicken-pressure-cooker/

postText:
Hi friends,

I work for a small Victorian charity called UBC Uncle Bobs Club   who raise funds for Children's health in Victoria. They are also the biggest contributing charity  partner to the Good Friday Appeal where we have 300+ volunteers assisting on the day. 

Each year, we reach out to business we already have partnerships with and ask for them to donate a gift for our volunteers to say thank you. This year, we would like to reach out to our local community's and support small businesses. 

Our idea this year is to provide grab bags for our volunteers. We would like to reach out to see if anyone would be interested in contributing to these bags. We are looking for vouchers, products, samples that we could place in the bags (even looking for bags!)
We will advertise your business on social media, on flyers, newsletters etc. You don't have to contribute that amount, we can arrange for your contribution to be allocated specifically (local, counting room etc)

If you would like to contribute please let me know here, DM me or email me on fundraising@ubcvic.org.au we can provide a fundraising letter to you.

Thank you 🙂

postText:
"I've been working with a client from California whose business specializes in wedding photography. Over the past year, I've helped him build over 1,000 backlinks on premium sites.
However, I've noticed two major concerns with his content strategy. First, he relies heavily on ChatGPT-generated articles, which can raise red flags with Google. Second, he focuses on optimizing for only one or two keywords, which can lead to keyword stuffing and over-optimization.

I warned him about these issues, especially since he's investing a significant amount in backlinks and sponsored posts through me. With my four years of SEO experience, I knew Google would eventually penalize his site.

Unfortunately, that's exactly what happened - Google flagged his website, causing it to plummet in rankings and lose significant traffic. I'm still disappointed, not just because he paid me for quality backlinks, but also because his mistakes undermined our collective efforts."🙄🙄

Does Google take into account the full URL of the site into the keywords of the page, or just whether the PAGE URL has the keywords?

example .com/commercial/blue-widgets

OR have all the keywords in the PAGE URL at the root level:
example .com/commercial-blue-widgets
example .com/commercial-red-widgets

What are your thoughts?

Ten Unknown Facts About #BMW
1. Founding and History: BMW, Bayerische Motoren Werke AG, was founded in 1916 in Munich, Germany, initially producing aircraft engines. The company transitioned to motorcycle production in the 1920s and eventually to automobiles in the 1930s.
2. Iconic Logo: The BMW logo, often referred to as the "roundel," consists of a black ring intersecting with four quadrants of blue and white. It represents the company's origins in aviation, with the blue and white symbolizing a spinning propeller against a clear blue sky.
3. Innovation in Technology: BMW is renowned for its innovations in automotive technology. It introduced the world's first electric car, the BMW i3, in 2013, and has been a leader in developing advanced driving assistance systems (ADAS) and hybrid powertrains.
4. Performance and Motorsport Heritage: BMW has a strong heritage in motorsport, particularly in touring car and Formula 1 racing. The brand's M division produces high-performance variants of their regular models, known for their precision engineering and exhilarating driving dynamics.
5. Global Presence: BMW is a global automotive Company
6. Luxury and Design: BMW is synonymous with luxury and distinctive design, crafting vehicles that blend elegance with cutting-edge technology and comfort.
7. Sustainable Practices: BMW has committed to sustainability, incorporating eco-friendly materials and manufacturing processes into its vehicles, as well as advancing electric vehicle technology with models like the BMW i4 and iX.
8. Global Manufacturing: BMW operates numerous production facilities worldwide, including in Germany, the United States, China, and other countries, ensuring a global reach and localized production.
9. Brand Portfolio: In addition to its renowned BMW brand, the company also owns MINI and Rolls-Royce, catering to a diverse range of automotive tastes and luxury segments.
10. Cultural Impact

postText:
PALM BEACH (The Borowitz Report)—In a series of scathing Truth Social posts on Tuesday, Donald J. Trump lambasted President Biden for issuing a pardon without being paid for it.
“Pardoning someone for free was an incredibly selfish act,” Trump wrote. “This will lower the market value of every future pardon I give.”
“The framers of the Constitution gave the president pardon power for one reason: to make money,” Trump continued. “I have too much respect for the Constitution to pardon people for free.”
In perhaps his strongest denunciation of Biden’s actions, he added, “Any decent father would have made Hunter ambassador to France.”

postText:
A DIVINE MESSAGE (2)
TO MR. DONALD J. TRUMP, MR. PUTIN, AND MR. ZELENSKY

To the Esteemed Leaders,

Your Excellencies,

In the divine light of Heaven, I, Thang Glofo, Global Peace Ambassador, humbly present to you the continuation of a profound message already shared. Humanity now stands on the threshold of a monumental transformation, transitioning from the discord and moral decline of a materialistic 3D world to a 4D quantum realm, where peace and virtue reign supreme.

To make this vision a reality, Heaven has decreed the establishment of KINGDOM OF GODS – the Alliance of Eighteen Nations: a transcendent, borderless nation without military forces, governed solely by principles of spirit and ethics. This is not merely a solution for our times but a sustainable foundation for millennia to come.

A Strategic Pathway to a New Era

1. Permanent Peace Treaty Between Russia and Ukraine

Peace between Russia and Ukraine is the cornerstone of the Kingdom of Gods. I, Thang Glofo, urge Mr. Putin and Mr. Zelensky to come together and sign a permanent peace treaty by January 2025.

A Historic Milestone: This will stand as undeniable evidence that peace triumphs over hatred.

Special Privileges: Both nations will be honored with exclusive membership in the Eighteen Holy States, a reward for their commitment to goodwill.

2. A Global Peace Treaty for 1,000 Years

Once peace is achieved between Russia and Ukraine, I, Thang Glofo, call upon all Heads of State to unite in signing a Global Peace Treaty, encompassing:

An Era Without War: A binding pledge to avoid all warfare for the next millennium.

3. The Formation of KINGDOM OF GODS – The Alliance of Eighteen Nations

With peace secured, the next step is the creation of KINGDOM OF GODS, which will entail:

1. Eighteen Nations: Only 18 countries will be selected, each donating one city, province, or state to form the Eighteen Holy States.

2. No Military Forces: This nation will stand as a testament to harmony and consensus under Heaven’s guidance.

3. A Global 4D Quantum Hub: KINGDOM OF GODS will be the emblem of wisdom, enlightenment, and global compassion.

A Special Appeal to Mr. Donald J. Trump

Your Excellency, with your unparalleled vision and global influence, I, Thang Glofo, humbly request that you become the Guardian Patron of this initiative. I, Thang Glofo, urge you to:

1. Lead Global Dialogues, selecting 18 deserving nations to contribute territory to KINGDOM OF GODS.

2. Prioritize Russia and Ukraine, allowing these nations to symbolize peace in January 2025.

3. Stand alongside me in creating a durable foundation for global peace.

Why KINGDOM OF GODS Is a ‘Miraculous Solution’ for Humanity

Restoring Global Ethics: Ending all conflicts while uniting humanity’s consciousness.

Sustainable Development: KINGDOM OF GODS will serve as a model for ethical and social progress, independent of materialism.

Elevating 4D Consciousness: Transforming humanity from self-interest to enlightenment, from discord to harmony.

A Closing Call to Action

Your Excellencies, I, Thang Glofo, implore you all to heed Heaven’s call. This is not just my mission; it is the shared responsibility of all who wield power and carry the burden of compassion in their hearts.

Together, let us forge a future for billions, a world devoid of war and suffering, illuminated only by light and virtue. KINGDOM OF GODS is not just a concept; it is a mission, a sacred summons for humanity to step into an era of eternal peace and prosperity.

With utmost respect,
THANG GLOFO
Global Peace Ambassador

postText:
A DIVINE MESSAGE
TO PRESIDENT DONALD J. TRUMP, PRESIDENT PUTIN, AND PRESIDENT ZELENSKY

Esteemed Leaders,

First and foremost, I extend my deepest respect to you, accompanied by great hope for a brighter future for humanity. I am Thang Glofo, Global Peace Ambassador, bearing a sacred message from the Supreme King, the Almighty God, to share with you an extraordinary vision: the establishment of the Alliance of Eighteen Nations, paving the way for a holy era under the banner of the KINGDOM OF GODS—a realm of peace, prosperity, and boundless joy.

---

A Sacred Mission: Creating the Kingdom of Gods

We stand at a pivotal juncture in human history. The crises we face today—from conflicts and wars to social instability and moral decline—are urgent calls from the Divine. This is the moment for humanity to go beyond temporary solutions and build a sustainable foundation rooted in global unity and alignment with the Divine Will.

President Donald J. Trump, I believe your strategic vision and profound influence are the keys to unlocking this new chapter. You have the opportunity to lead historic dialogues with the leaders of 18 nations, forming an unprecedented alliance. In this vision, each nation contributes a city, province, or state to create the 18 United States of the Kingdom of Gods. This will serve as a profound symbol of unity, morality, and collective dedication to humanity's highest aspirations.

President Putin and President Zelensky, I respectfully invite you to come together, resolve all differences, and sign a Permanent Peace Treaty in January 2025. When two nations, once at odds, transform into friendly neighbors and join the Alliance of Eighteen Nations, the world will witness a monumental act of reconciliation and unity.

---

Unified Consciousness: The Key to Peace

Dear Leaders, we do not lack power; we lack groundbreaking ideas and global unity to achieve a UNIFIED CONSCIOUSNESS with the DIVINE. The Divine does not wish for humanity to be divided by borders, religions, or races. Instead, we are encouraged to transcend these limitations and unite to create a prosperous world anchored in peace.

The KINGDOM OF GODS is not merely an idea; it is a Divine mandate, designed to lead humanity into the 4D Quantum Era. This is a transformative period in which human consciousness evolves from selfishness and conflict to enlightenment, love, and harmony.

---

Awakening Humanity to Transcendence

We live in a dreamlike state dominated by ego, greed, and anger. But you, as leaders of immense compassion and foresight, can help open the door of enlightenment for all humanity. When we awaken, a new world will emerge. It will be a world where individuals and nations alike thrive in peace, unparalleled progress, and moral integrity under the Divine's radiant guidance.

President Putin and President Zelensky, I urge you to lay down all enmity and "lower the sword, become as saints." This is not just an opportunity to end war but also to become symbols of the greatest reconciliation in human history.

---

The Alliance of Eighteen Nations: Humanity’s Glorious Future

The Alliance of Eighteen Nations will serve as the cornerstone for humanity's progress in this new era. This will be a global governance system led by individuals of goodwill, vision, and virtue. The unity among these nations will usher humanity into an age of enduring prosperity, where all live in morality, peace, and happiness.

The KINGDOM OF GODS is not merely a dream; it is a sacred mission entrusted to us by the Divine. Once we unite, all blessings and grace from the Divine will flow abundantly to humanity, guiding us through challenges to achieve true fulfillment.

---

A Final Call to Action

Today, I invite you to join me in taking action. Let us transcend the boundaries of fear and selfishness. Let us allow the hearts of humanity to connect with the light of the Divine and together build an era of peace, morality, and unprecedented prosperity.

Yours in peace and purpose,

Respectfully,
Thang Glofo
Global Peace Ambassador

postText:
The Need for Bipartisan Politics in the United States For A Path Back To Democracy

Hate is often rooted in social, cultural, or political contexts, where individuals may develop negative stereotypes and beliefs about each other based on group characteristics in both parties. Which is one of the definitions of Prejudice and Discrimination.

In an era marked by increasing political polarization, the division within the United States is becoming more pronounced. The sharp divide in ideologies, values, and priorities between the two major political parties has created a climate of contention that hampers legislative progress and fuels societal discord. 

As a Democratic Republic, our government is designed to function effectively through bipartisan collaboration. For the sake of effective governance and national cohesion, it is imperative to return to bipartisan politics an approach centered on cooperation, compromise, and mutual respect, rather than rigid adherence to partisan ideologies.

Over the past few decades, American politics has experienced a significant increase in polarization. According to a 2021 Pew Research Center study, the ideological gap between Republicans and Democrats has widened considerably. 

Both parties have increasingly embraced extreme views, often perceiving their opponents as existential threats to the country. 

This divisiveness translates into legislative gridlock, where essential bills stall in Congress due to a lack of bipartisan support.

This atmosphere of conflict breeds further division among the electorate. As individuals become entrenched in their political identities, they often align with like-minded others on social media and community platforms, amplifying echo chambers that reinforce their beliefs. This phenomenon can lead to a decrease in cross-party dialogue and understanding, exacerbating the already deep rifts within society.

Bipartisan politics is not merely a goal but a necessary framework for achieving workable solutions that benefit all Americans. Contrary to the misconception that bipartisan politics requires one party to sacrifice its principles, it actually encourages negotiation and collaboration, allowing for the integration of diverse perspectives into legislation. In a Democratic Republic, our Constitution is predicated on the idea that both parties can work towards accomplishing their platforms through dialogue and cooperation, without altering their underlying principles.

Defining bipartisanship involves cooperation between both major political parties to pass legislation that reflects a compromise between differing priorities. This process recognizes the value of diverse ideas, where both parties can contribute to shaping effective policies that serve the public interest. Bipartisan cooperation does not mean changing the fundamental platforms of the parties; instead, it allows each party to pursue its goals while acknowledging the legitimate concerns and aspirations of the other.

The Role of concessions in the context of bipartisan politics signifies mutual give-and-take. When one party concedes a particular demand, it paves the way for the other party to do the same, leading to solutions that address the concerns of multiple stakeholders. Importantly, just because an issue is not resolved in one bill does not mean it is permanently off the table; it can re-emerge in future legislation.

While there is a growing sentiment among some factions of the Republican Party that aligns with the “Make America Great Again” (MAGA) movement, it is essential to recognize that not all Republicans subscribe to this ideology. True Republicans, representing a more traditional and moderate strain of the party, are often more amenable to collaboration and negotiation with Democrats.

True Republicans understand the importance of bipartisan governance and are interested in addressing the needs of their constituents—regardless of the partisan affiliations of those constituents. As bipartisan politics gains traction, it may empower these traditional Republicans to step forward, reassert their influence, and advocate for a more collaborative approach in Congress.

Despite the challenges posed by MAGA-aligned factions that resist compromise, there is still hope for bipartisan efforts to flourish. If advocates for bipartisan politics can galvanize support among traditional Republicans, it could signal to the larger electorate—particularly the millions of original Republicans who may feel disenfranchised—that there is a viable path forward.

Encouraging traditional Republicans can act as a rallying call for original Republicans who have become disheartened by the extremism often associated with the MAGA movement. By emphasizing the importance of returning to foundational values of cooperation and mutual respect, these voters can be encouraged to stand up and demand a change in their party’s direction.

Reinforcing the power of votes is another key aspect. If a significant number of original Republicans coalesce around bipartisan initiatives, they can wield substantial political power within the party. Their collective voice at the ballot box could challenge MAGA leadership, reinforcing the message that compromise and reasonable discourse are not only preferable but essential for effective governance.

Creating a viable voting block is another potential outcome. Just as the 2020 elections showcased the rise of diverse coalitions within the Democratic Party, there is potential for a similar phenomenon among Republicans. If the party can cultivate an environment where traditional Republican ideals thrive alongside urgent bipartisan efforts, it may attract not only party loyalists but also independents and moderate Democrats seeking effective governance free from extreme partisanship.

Enhanced legislative productivity is one of the most significant advantages of bipartisan politics. With cooperation, Congress can move beyond gridlock and pass crucial laws on various pressing issues, including healthcare, education, infrastructure, and climate change. Legislation that garners support from both conservatives and liberals is more likely to be robust and sustainable.

Restoration of public trust is another vital benefit. Bipartisan efforts can help restore the public’s trust in government institutions. Voter disengagement and cynicism are often rooted in perceptions of partisanship as self-serving rather than as a means to serve the public good. When citizens see their representatives working across the aisle, they may come to believe that collaboration is possible and that their elected officials are dedicated to addressing the needs of their constituents.

Social cohesion is a further advantage. The tangible benefits of bipartisan politics extend beyond legislative achievements; they also contribute to social cohesion. When political leaders model collaboration, they send a powerful message about the potential for unity amid diversity. This, in turn, can inspire citizens to engage in constructive dialogue across political lines, leading to a more informed and resilient citizenry.

Historically, the United States has thrived when bipartisan efforts led to significant accomplishments. Landmark legislation such as the Civil Rights Act of 1964 and the bipartisan agreement on the Marshall Plan exemplify how collaboration can lead to transformative change that resonates throughout the fabric of society.

Today’s political climate necessitates a recommitment to bipartisanship, requiring leaders to prioritize the nation’s well-being above partisan loyalties. Grassroots movements that promote dialogue and relationship-building among diverse groups can empower citizens and lobby for elected officials who are dedicated to fostering bipartisanship.

As division within the United States continues to escalate, the call for bipartisan politics has never been more urgent. 

While the MAGA faction may resist compromise and collaboration, true Republicans have the potential to lead the charge for bipartisan efforts, encouraging others to join in pursuit of a more unified approach to governance. In the Democratic Republic, both parties must work together to achieve their respective goals, ensuring our governmental system and Constitution function effectively. 

Through collaboration, mutual respect, and a willingness to find common ground, Congress can move beyond partisan strife into a realm where legislation reflects the needs and aspirations of all Americans. 

This commitment to unity, The Constitution, and the Democratic Republic will ultimately yield a more functional government, restored trust in political institutions, and a stronger, more cohesive society. 

As we look toward a future filled with challenges, bipartisan politics may be the beacon of hope required to guide the nation toward a better tomorrow.

postText:
Singapore’s #genz workers are challenging traditional workplace norms, prioritizing hybrid work & work-life balance. A recent IWG study highlights this revolutionary shift in workplace expectations.
Only 12% of #genz in #singapore want full-time office work, while 61% find spending 2–3 days in the office most productive. #hybrid setups are becoming the new standard.
This shift is disrupting workplace conventions, forcing organizations to rethink strategies to attract & retain top talent. It’s time for leaders to adapt or risk losing valuable employees.

More on the same in our article:
https://www.theworkersrights.com/gen-z-in-singapore-demands-hybrid-work-prioritizing-flexibility-and-work-life-balance/

postText:
Belgium made history as the first country to grant labor rights to sex workers. Rights like sick days, maternity pay, and pensions are now available, marking a global milestone!
Sex workers in #belgium can sign #employment contracts, gaining rights to refuse clients, set conditions for acts, or stop at any time for safety. This ensures dignity and protection in their work.
However, these protections only apply to workers with employment contracts. Self-employed workers and those in pornography or striptease remain excluded. Progress continues, but gaps persist.

More on the same in our article:
https://www.theworkersrights.com/belgium-makes-history-first-country-to-ensure-labour-rights-and-protections-for-sex-workers/

#belgium #labourrights #SexWorkerRights #globalequality #legalprogress #labor #workplaceprotections 
#inclusivelaws 
#humanrightsmatter 
#socialreforms 
#employmentequality 
#GlobalHistoryMade

postText:
The Syrian crisis enters its 14th year, leaving 16.7 million people needing protection and humanitarian aid. With 7.2M internally displaced people and 6.2M refugees, it's one of the worst global displacement crises.
Most #Refugees are in Egypt, Iraq, Jordan, Lebanon, & Turkey—facing poverty, uncertainty, and rising social tensions. Refugees face daily challenges: lack of work, restrictive regulations, and deteriorating protection in host nations.
The UNHCR's relief efforts include legal aid, financial support, and fundamental protection services. Aid remains critical as spontaneous returns to Syria persist, despite worsening conditions in the region.

More on the same in our article:
https://www.theworkersrights.com/syrian-refugees-struggle-deepens-as-fighting-escalates/

#Syrian #Refugees #HumanitarianAid  #MiddleEastConflict #GlobalRelief #UNHCRSupport #DisplacementCrisis #ResettlementNeeds #AidForRefugees #CrisisResponse #HumanRightsAction #RefugeesWelcome

postText:
Students at Atlantic College, St Donats, are leading a fight to save migrants at sea. These passionate individuals are volunteering to address the urgent humanitarian crisis caused by perilous sea crossings.
The Mediterranean remains the most dangerous #Migration path, claiming 2,000 lives in 2024 alone. Inspired by personal stories and global challenges, these students are training in marine rescues, saving lives in an increasingly urgent crisis.
By learning essential skills like boat building and rescue operations, #AtlanticCollege students aim to become the next generation of #humanitarian champions.

postText:
The following wave of fighting in #syria threatens to produce another wave of #migration across Europe. The civil war that decorates Syria had made more than 13 million people flee their homes, and around 6.5 million of them fled to other countries in search of refuge.

They started moving to #Europe; for instance, they remembered 2015, when over one million #Refugees were there. Europe’s resources are still under pressure, with the #asylum systems and other services still under pressure.

Some countries have been affected most, including #germany , Austria, and Sweden, which have been accommodating families who fled from wars, economic crises, and natural calamities such as the 2023 #earthquake .

Of course, #Migration pressure does not decrease as the conflict continues indefinitely, and it will continue to grow. This is likely to widen political polarization in the EU in terms of #refugeepolicy and asylum-seeking regime.

commentText: Burn notice is almost always not enough liquid.  If you get that message, it is OK to open the top, but you do still need to make sure the pressure has gone down first.  Check the valve and make sure it's not still popped up.    Generally...if it just says "pressure cook", it means at high pressure.  The quick cooking of your recipe may well have been due to the lack of water.  It caused the unit to get hotter than it should have, hence the "burn notice"

postText: Sounds interesting, but being white chocolate is a no for me
commentText: After doing the water test PLEASE remember that the Instant Pot is NOT instant. Sure, your food cooks faster BUT the pot has to come up to pressure before it starts 'cooking' the food and depending on how much is in your pot that can take 10 minutes or more. ALSO after it is done cooking you need to allow some time for the pot to come down from being under pressure and that TOO can take time. SURE you can release pressure right away (NOT for meat unless you want a tough roast) but even that takes a few minutes. Be SURE that you release the pressure AWAY from things like your cupboards unless you want to give them a hot steam treatment. 🙂 And EH, have fun.

Just dump the ingredients in the right order and do NOT stir before cooking. 
Warning: we don’t like to order pasta Alfredo when we go out anymore because this is so good.

I do sauté shrimp or sliced chicken in skillet while waiting on the 8 minute natural release. 
It’s so delicious.

postText: Lest we forget ❤️
commentText:
It affects the boiling point of the water as the pressure releases.

When pressure cooking, the boiling point rises, so the water gets even hotter than 212 degrees F before boiling. When a Quick Release is done, the pressure drops quickly, causing the boiling point to drop very rapidly and the super heated water comes to a rapid boil. If you are cooking meat in particular, the boiling water than draws out the moisture and flavor from the meat. You’ll wind up with a flavorful broth, but your meat will most likely turn out tough and stringy.

Doing a 15 to 20 minute Natural Release, or even a full Natural Release if the pot is very full, allows both the pressure and water temperature to drop slowly, so the liquid doesn’t come back to a boil while pressure is dropping. This allows the meat to rest while the pressure and water temperature is dropping and it should remain tender and juicy.

postText: Same in Adelaide
commentText: There's a root vegetable grown in the mountains of West Virginia by descendants of Dutch settlers called the Hanover.  It's like a larger, but uglier, cousin of the rutabaga.  It has little roots and protuberances sticking out all over, and isn't uniformly rounded.  It obviously isn't produced commercially because of its appearance, but it's tastier than the rutabaga.  I hope this heirloom vegetable hasn't disappeared.  It was in the mid-1970s that I tasted it.

postText:
Anthony Jaggar, don’t listen to people that are saying disavow the links and simply ignore the “toxicity score”

Disavowing the links only makes your site worse. The reason being, Google can't tell the difference between "toxic" links and "good links" so when we disavow Google stops counting the authority that we were once getting from those links. I know it sounds weird but trust me. We would only disavow or do anything with those toxic links if we see a "Manual Action" item in GSC.

The “toxic” link themselves don't negatively impact your site. The proof of that is if these "toxic" links were negatively impacting your site then the competitors would just pay SEOs to link toxic links to your site.

Here you can read more: https://linkbuilder.io/disavow-backlinks/#:~:text=It%20has%20the%20potential%20to,contributing%20to%20your%20site's%20authority.

“The history of the Pago jewelry brand began in the mid-1950s in San Francisco, California. In the vintage jewelry market, products marked “Pago” are extremely rare. Unfortunately, there is no much information about the company and its founders. One of the reasons for this uncertainty is the short life of the company, less than one decade.
Noteworthy, according to the 1959 US Catalog of Copyright Entries, the company patented several jewelry designs. Among them, in particular, bracelets made of metal and jewels with animal design charms. Also, the company’s jewelers created brooches, pendants and earrings using gold-tone metal alloys, pewter, rhinestones, art glass and faux pearls. The maker’s mark on oval cartouche includes the word “Pago” in capital letters and a copyright sign.
The company ceased to exist in the mid-1960s.”

postText: Hi Brian - step 1: On-page SEO is a myth. Yes, there is a lot you can do (or rather, forget to do that is counter productive) but you are taking the wrong approach. You are talking about snippets vs descriptions. Putting in more keywords into your page will just expand the number of indices (an index is a list of sites, in rank order, that match a keyword or key phrase). Taking one page and spanning multiple indices stretches whatever authority you have across them. Evaluate your competition - chances are really good that in a highly competitive, high volume + high intent that the pages ranking above you are either very authoratative or very narrow (read: focused). If you had a lot of authority, chances are low that you'd be asking the question. 99% of "keyword" questions stem from a lack of understanding (or even denial of the understanding) of how Authority works.

postText:
Nancy Mikyska most of the responses you will get are generic theory or the person is using ChatGPT to answer you.

Nobody in the universe can answer you correctly because we don’t know;
- does the page rank for anything now

- what volume of traffic does it get now, meaning if it gets 1,000,000 visits vs 100 what context would a drop in traffic be

- does it rank for anything relevant to what you are trying to get traffic for

- how long is it vs how short the new one will be

- once you make it shorter what keywords are being removed or added plus do they have any relevance to the content

- will the URL change too, then have better or worse relevance to the content on page or your site overall

- are you changing any other elements of content on the page? If is just a title it may not even get re-indexed

postText:
Roshan Ambler as a marketing consultant this is seriously one of the biggest load of garbage that I hear come out of agencies via clients that come to me for help. If a particular site or content piece is written well enough and ranks, then it will get found for 10, 30, 50 or even more keyword variations, so as others have mentioned if you do your job well you literally cannot 'limit' the keywords that you win

Many agencies try and scale their packages of course based on how many keywords they are supposedly targeting but that may or may not make sense depending on the business as some may have very diverse services or maybe just one service.

Most business owners have no idea about digital marketing so it is easy to get away with this strategy as humans we are used to being able to look & compare offers that have quantifiable elements. Although at the same time it then makes it easy to then compare on price vs value/expertise so it becomes a double edged sword.

The difficulty of the work will also vary e.g service business in local area with low competition vs one that is saturated or product sold nationally via eComm etc so those scenarios should be considered, really there should be different solutions for each

Therefore the more commercially sensible approach is to have an offer structured around the scenario of the client and their goal specifically. I realise this doesn't give you a black/white answer but this is such a generic question it is impossible

So ultimately while it sounds complex the ultimate answer is probably offering a typical 'keyword limit' based offer which is a set structure together with customised packages together with a free consult session to work out which one might be more suitable to that person then a heap of case studies showing how different approaches worked

postText:
Your site is being put in front of more people (impressions), but some of those appearances might not rank as highly for your newly attracted searchers. 

Your original audience are likely seeing you exactly as they did before, but your new audience who don't see you ranking as highly as the existing group will be what's affecting the average rank. Where one line goes up and the other goes down, it's just the normal interplay between number of searches you appear in and the average rank across all of those searches. If the BOTH go up or down over time that's more significant.

The main thing though, are your clicks going up or down? Really that's all that matters!
